column3: My direct team leader is a great role model for AIESECers.
column4: We foster an inclusive environment within the team.
column5: I enjoy doing my work and am empowered to do my best here.
column6: I feel empowered to take on further leadership development experiences.
column7: My team is capable of balancing short term outcomes and long term gains.
column8: I've had the space to learn by practicing some of the activities in my job description with my team leader's assistance in the beginning of our term.
column9: Our team working times are the perfect moments for us to synergize, solve common problems, and learn from each other so we become more productive.
column10: My accomplishments are recognized by others in the organization.
column11: My team has a routine to hold myself and others accountable for our results.
column12: I have a clear and challenging goal that contributes to the success of our team.
column13: I understand the current state of my team (facts and data) every month, I understand what we want to achieve as a team by the end of the term, and I understand what we need to improve to achieve it.
column14: My job performance and behavior are evaluated fairly.
column15: I have reviewed my personal development plan with my direct team leader, it helps me to understand my current achievement, gaps, and ways forward.
column16: My direct team leader provides me spaces to develop my leadership qualities.
column17: My team has team meetings to keep everyone aware of relevant information with clear calls to action.
column18: My team leader provides me a one-to-one space monthly to review how am I doing (personally and in AIESEC) and find the scope for improvement.
column19: I am more eager to work because I'm able to connect to my team.
column20: My team leader and teammates give valuable feedback on my work that helps me to improve.
